"nioEventLoopGroup-6-3" #64 prio=10 os_prio=31 tid=0x00007fe80da43800 nid=0x720b runnable [0x0000700003bfb000]
   java.lang.Thread.State: RUNNABLE
	at java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap.get(ConcurrentHashMap.java:936)
	at org.apache.ratis.server.storage.LogSegment.getEntryWithoutLoading(LogSegment.java:293)
	at org.apache.ratis.server.storage.SegmentedRaftLog.get(SegmentedRaftLog.java:185)
	at org.apache.ratis.logservice.server.LogStateMachine.processReadRequest(LogStateMachine.java:304)
	at org.apache.ratis.logservice.server.LogStateMachine.query(LogStateMachine.java:210)
	at org.apache.ratis.server.impl.RaftServerImpl.submitClientRequestAsync(RaftServerImpl.java:527)
	at org.apache.ratis.server.impl.RaftServerImpl.submitClientRequest(RaftServerImpl.java:592)
	at org.apache.ratis.server.impl.RaftServerProxy.submitClientRequest(RaftServerProxy.java:331)
```

Looking at the API for RaftLog, I feel like we might be conflating "index" arguments to mean different things. I think that index on RaftLog might be an index to the segment, whereas we're using the index to mean offset into the total log. Still digging...
